layers on a circular field with a central pitch. It originated in England and enjoys massive popularity in South Asia, Australia, and the Caribbean, with the T20 format growing rapidly.", "Basketball is a team sport played on a rectangular court where two teams of five players each try to score by shooting a ball through the opponent's hoop. Founded by James Naismith in 1891, the NBA showcases the world's elite talent.", "Rugby is a full-contact team sport that originated in England in the 19th century, played with an oval ball by two teams of 15 players. The Rugby World Cup is the sport's premier international competition with dominant nations like New Zealand and South Africa.", "Volleyball is a team sport where two teams of six players separate by a net try to score points by grounding the ball on the opponent's side. Indoor volleyball and beach volleyball are both Olympic sports with distinct rules."], "scores": [0.8957377753828543, 0.857883028843369, 0.8391499538244638, 0.8383490978777826, 0.8361295091699534], "model_name": "gte-small", "document_ids": ["Soccer", "Cricket", "Basketball", "Rugby", "Volleyball"]}}